  "texts": [
    "Lastly, news article summaries typically cover key information into about 100 words, a scientific paper summary needs to comprehensively summarize content from multiple sections, often exceeding 200 words and sometimes reaching up to 400 words (Oh et al., 2023).",
    "These differences pose challenges that current methods unsuitable for direct application to automatic summarization of scientific papers.",
    "Existing methods to improving scientific paper summarization primarily focus on two research directions.",
    "The first direction aims to extracting key information to reduce the length of papers.",
    "Techniques such as topic models or heterogeneous trees are commonly used by researchers to selectively extract important words or sentence from the text."
